00:39:53,595 --> 00:40:02,962
Um, I spoke before you on April 11th and I asked the committee to have a transparent succession plan for the position of superintendent in place by June of this year.

234
00:40:04,143 --> 00:40:11,408
On May 3rd, I attended the city council meeting and was very surprised to learn that in the superintendent's contract,

235
00:40:11,987 --> 00:40:17,749
It states that the school committee shall advise the superintendent of its intent to extend his contract by June 30, 2016.

236
00:40:19,950 --> 00:40:25,953
I was disappointed to hear this from a city counselor given the fact four committee members were part of the negotiations for the current contract.

237
00:40:26,893 --> 00:40:30,695
That information could have been relayed to me when I spoke on April 11th.

238
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:35,457
With that being said, I would assume the committee will have a plan in place by the given date.

239
00:40:35,777 --> 00:40:38,858
This is probably the most important role that you as a school committee member

240
00:40:39,430 --> 00:40:40,391
will play in your tenure.

241
00:40:40,591 --> 00:40:42,192
It's your legacy as elected officials.

242
00:40:42,893 --> 00:40:44,854
You can get this right or you can get this very wrong.

243
00:40:46,015 --> 00:40:51,179
I followed up with each of you individually via email, and again, did not receive a response from the majority of you.

244
00:40:51,679 --> 00:40:53,200
From those that did respond, thank you.

245
00:40:54,481 --> 00:40:59,485
What I'm asking from you is to devise a plan in the event Medford needs to hire a new superintendent.

246
00:40:59,545 --> 00:41:02,727
You've not been faced with such a task in over 20 years.

247
00:41:03,748 --> 00:41:07,751
And if the need did arise any time soon, you would have no guidelines set forth.

248
00:41:08,569 --> 00:41:13,574
Such a situation would surely result in panic and a haphazard process of finding a replacement.

249
00:41:14,515 --> 00:41:17,058
Ultimately, this is not about Mr. Belson's contract.

250
00:41:17,518 --> 00:41:21,102
However, the fact that it is the catalyst for such a discussion cannot be ignored.

251
00:41:21,923 --> 00:41:25,066
I'm speaking to you as a citizen you have been elected to represent.

252
00:41:25,987 --> 00:41:28,369
I'm also speaking to you on behalf of the 250 other residents

253
00:41:30,109 --> 00:41:32,450
that have signed both an online and paper petition.

254
00:41:32,971 --> 00:41:42,376
I'm frustrated a petition had to be started asking you to do your due diligence and ensure that proper measures are being taken regarding filling one of the most important positions in our school system.

255
00:41:42,916 --> 00:41:47,539
This is not just a small group of people with a sudden sense of urgency that are concerned about this.

256
00:41:48,219 --> 00:41:51,961
These are your constituents, and this is a plan that should always have been in place.

257
00:41:52,962 --> 00:41:58,305
With all of that being said, I will reiterate the questions I have regarding the process for renewal.

258
00:41:58,907 --> 00:42:01,589
and the subsequent questions should a contract not be renewed.

259
00:42:02,190 --> 00:42:04,852
Please feel free to take notes and answer when I'm done speaking.

260
00:42:05,393 --> 00:42:11,839
As I said before, this plan is not just about this contract, but since this contract is the one being renewed, it needs to be addressed.

261
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:17,364
I understand Mr. Belson is currently working on a self-evaluation as stated in his contract.

262
00:42:18,004 --> 00:42:21,127
I further understand you will then begin your process of evaluation.

263
00:42:21,696 --> 00:42:30,101
Given you are obligated to work on this as a committee, at what point do you discuss your evaluations if the superintendent is always present at every meeting and every executive session?

264
00:42:31,122 --> 00:42:34,644
Is this process made public and is there an opportunity for public input?

265
00:42:35,665 --> 00:42:43,230
Is Mr. Belson's contract automatically extended on June 30th if your evaluations determine he is performing in a satisfactory manner?

266
00:42:44,291 --> 00:42:47,713
At this point, I feel your lack of a succession plan will truly come into play.

267
00:42:48,353 --> 00:42:51,235
If Mr. Belson announces at a later date that he plans on retiring,

268
00:42:51,689 --> 00:42:52,469
What is your plan?

269
00:42:53,550 --> 00:42:55,210
A plan should answer the following questions.

270
00:42:55,930 --> 00:43:01,552
What are the guidelines put forth with respect to renewing the superintendent's contract and finding a replacement?

271
00:43:02,292 --> 00:43:19,738
These guidelines should include, but not be limited to, evaluation of the current superintendent as set forth by the terms in his contract, allowing the school committee to do their own evaluation and discuss said evaluations without the superintendent present, gathering input from the community regarding their evaluations,

272
00:43:20,478 --> 00:43:26,522
If the contract is renewed, it should be clearly documented how recent and longstanding issues within the school system will be addressed.

273
00:43:27,923 --> 00:43:33,087
Clearly stated and documented requirements for a successor should be put forth.

274
00:43:34,268 --> 00:43:41,673
The guidelines should coherently document what the initiatives and direction of Medford Public Schools are and how they will be sustained by a successor.

275
00:43:42,854 --> 00:43:49,539
You need to evaluate the potential for an internal replacement and the eligibility requirements for such a vertical career move.

276
00:43:50,675 --> 00:43:59,718
You need to establish a timeline for searching for and transitioning in a replacement, allowing time for a replacement to work alongside the current superintendent if possible.

277
00:44:01,219 --> 00:44:06,220
And lastly, you need to determine how to record and maintain the knowledge that Mr. Belson does currently possess.

278
00:44:06,961 --> 00:44:11,422
It's a vast amount of knowledge and it's a vast network that he has created.

279
00:44:12,202 --> 00:44:14,123
And you need to know how to relay that to a successor.

280
00:44:15,147 --> 00:44:19,431
What I'm proposing should be a matter of routine governing within the realm of the school committee.

281
00:44:20,132 --> 00:44:27,740
As stated by one resident who signed the petition, succession planning is critical for a smooth search and leadership transition.

282
00:44:28,281 --> 00:44:30,143
We need the school committee to be proactive.

283
00:44:30,823 --> 00:44:37,210
As our elected representatives, they should implement a thoughtful, transparent process that prioritizes community input.

284
00:44:38,562 --> 00:44:44,224
I urge you to complete this process sooner rather than later and avoid the possibility of panic in our school system.

285
00:44:44,784 --> 00:44:50,525
There is indeed a sense of urgency since a proper search and transition should a replacement be needed will likely take a year.

286
00:44:51,225 --> 00:44:55,487
Now is the time you should be organizing yourselves and preparing yourself to take action if necessary.

287
00:44:56,327 --> 00:44:56,627
Thank you.

288
00:44:58,468 --> 00:44:58,628
Ms.

289
00:44:58,648 --> 00:44:59,008
Cuneo.

290
00:45:00,028 --> 00:45:00,369
Thank you.

291
00:45:01,029 --> 00:45:01,629
And thank you, Ms.

292
00:45:01,669 --> 00:45:06,310
Moore for coming here again and bringing your concerns to us.

293
00:45:06,670 --> 00:45:07,871
And I respect that.

294
00:45:09,271 --> 00:45:13,572
I'm going to address something in the room that maybe no one wants to talk about.

295
00:45:13,632 --> 00:45:19,294
And that is the elephant in the room, the rumors, the Facebook posts, the discussions between constituents.

296
00:45:20,111 --> 00:45:21,952
and not to mention the City Council.

297
00:45:22,613 --> 00:45:30,658
As a member of the School Committee, I truly want to thank you and I want to thank anyone who is truly concerned and has a vested interest in this situation.

298
00:45:31,399 --> 00:45:35,742
I love the idea of having people come up and discuss their ideas, for this is the forum.

299
00:45:36,504 --> 00:45:38,085
where this discussion should be held.

300
00:45:38,846 --> 00:45:50,635
However, I also want to remind everyone as a school committee member, there is a process and a succession of what we as a body need and decide to discuss and determine for the best interest of our district.

301
00:45:51,296 --> 00:45:56,640
As a committee member or anyone who needs to compare and evaluate, we need to compare one year to the next.

302
00:45:57,361 --> 00:45:59,462
And we are in the process of collecting that data.

303
00:46:00,343 --> 00:46:05,027
Now, as far as transparency, let's address what maybe I took for granted

304
00:46:06,672 --> 00:46:07,432
That was obvious.

305
00:46:08,473 --> 00:46:10,554
I will speak for myself as a school committee member.

306
00:46:11,235 --> 00:46:31,886
After investing 10 years, completed years, nine years as MASC, as a member, executive board member, and not to mention the president of Massachusetts Association of School Committees, meaning that I represent of all the school committee members in the state, the projects, the money, the time, the networking in our city, across the state and country,

307
00:46:32,462 --> 00:46:47,972
We have invested, and I hope and think parents, students, administrators, teachers, and constituents in our district would not believe that we, as your elected officials, would have been given this position and will take the hiring of a new superintendent very lightly.

308
00:46:49,012 --> 00:47:00,860
The hiring of superintendent, especially under our circumstances, whatever you agree or disagree, like or dislike the superintendent, the gentleman has been in a position for many years.

309
00:47:01,740 --> 00:47:03,621
For some of you, that may be a con.

310
00:47:04,142 --> 00:47:05,583
For some, it may be a pro.

311
00:47:06,804 --> 00:47:17,611
Personal preference, but for a person who has been around, and I can honestly say and tell you I've been on many sides and have seen our administration work, where many of you have not,

312
00:47:18,618 --> 00:47:22,003
I can tell you we have and are represented very well across the state.

313
00:47:22,844 --> 00:47:24,666
I know this is not the point for many of you.

314
00:47:25,047 --> 00:47:27,210
You are asking for transparency in the process.

315
00:47:27,971 --> 00:47:33,839
Educated in what the superintendent search entails and knowing what other cities are going through right now,

316
00:47:35,253 --> 00:47:39,357
This is something that we as a school committee need to sit down and discuss.

317
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:45,602
We have had certain maybe not official meetings, but the discussion has come up.

318
00:47:46,043 --> 00:47:48,485
But we need to have certain things done in succession.

319
00:47:49,206 --> 00:47:53,089
As I mentioned before, the superintendent has already spoken to us.

320
00:47:53,249 --> 00:47:59,775
We already knew when the evaluation is going to be presented to us as far as what the next step was going to be.

321
00:48:03,475 --> 00:48:09,423
And so I guess at this point, I just really want to say that we are very much aware of what's going on.

322
00:48:09,984 --> 00:48:17,635
And it's kind of frustrating as a school committee member to sit there and know the hard work that people in our city have done.

323
00:48:18,588 --> 00:48:22,669
The children that were here tonight, that shows what we have in our schools.

324
00:48:23,209 --> 00:48:26,170
Not only in the group that was here this evening, but in many groups.

325
00:48:26,270 --> 00:48:34,652
This last month and a half, we have done nothing but give certificates out, not from us, but what our children have achieved in the state of Massachusetts.

326
00:48:35,152 --> 00:48:42,714
So to sit and listen over and over again, to listen to people just throw things out that are not factual is very frustrating.

327
00:48:43,215 --> 00:48:47,916
So with all due respect, I do and ask that I make a motion this evening

328
00:48:48,596 --> 00:48:55,941
that we have the meeting of the superintendent committee of the whole for the superintendent's evaluation.

329
00:48:56,481 --> 00:49:07,668
And then we also need to have the meeting of executive, the executive meeting, I'm sorry, the executive committee of, executive meeting for his contract.

330
00:49:09,509 --> 00:49:10,850
If I could just make an announcement.

331
00:49:23,078 --> 00:49:25,479
If I could just make one announcement.

332
00:49:25,539 --> 00:49:33,423
We have scheduled a Committee of the Whole for June 2nd to go over the superintendent's self-review of himself.

333
00:49:34,103 --> 00:49:38,725
And at that point, we will be evaluating him, and then we will move forward in the process.

334
00:49:39,405 --> 00:49:46,949
I would just like to follow up to that to say that I am actually a very proud product of Medford Public Schools.

335
00:49:47,209 --> 00:49:49,270
My children attend Medford Public Schools.

336
00:49:49,470 --> 00:49:51,491
I am extraordinarily aware

337
00:49:52,116 --> 00:49:57,042
of what Medford Public Schools have done, what they can do, and I hope to God what they will do.

338
00:49:57,823 --> 00:50:04,191
So for you to sit there and say that I don't appreciate what goes on in the Medford Public Schools is an outright travesty.

339
00:50:04,592 --> 00:50:08,417
With that being said, I am not asking you

340
00:50:09,072 --> 00:50:13,296
to simply sit there and say if you're going to renew or not renew Mr. Belson's contract.

341
00:50:13,336 --> 00:50:18,079
What I'm asking you is to have a transparent process if it has to happen.

342
00:50:18,640 --> 00:50:22,863
If, God forbid, he couldn't perform his job tomorrow, what is the process?

343
00:50:23,284 --> 00:50:24,705
And you'll say it's transparent.

344
00:50:24,745 --> 00:50:31,911
Well, then why did I stand here in front of you in April and not one of you had the audacity, not one of you could say anything to me?

345
00:50:32,391 --> 00:50:33,852
You didn't acknowledge that I was here.

346
00:50:34,933 --> 00:50:36,615
So don't tell me that's transparent.

347
00:50:38,054 --> 00:50:39,135
Thank you, Mr. Benedetto.

348
00:50:39,595 --> 00:50:39,995
Thank you.

349
00:50:40,396 --> 00:50:41,036
Thank you.

350
00:50:41,356 --> 00:50:42,717
Point of personal privilege, Ms.

351
00:50:42,737 --> 00:50:43,138
Cuno.

352
00:50:43,578 --> 00:50:45,019
Angela, I didn't say it was you.

353
00:50:45,159 --> 00:50:45,960
I'm saying in general.

354
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:47,160
Well, I'm the one standing up.

355
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:55,927
Actually, I said thank you to you when you first came, and I said it a couple of times, actually, that I enjoy that when you do come, this is where the forum should be.

356
00:50:56,647 --> 00:51:03,172
It's very, very frustrating to be on this side, too, just as much as it is for you that you want to do the best you possibly can for your children.

357
00:51:03,872 --> 00:51:10,384
But it's very frustrating on this side working the hours that everybody works, not just me, I'm no one compared to everybody in this room.

358
00:51:11,286 --> 00:51:16,115
But to sit here week after week and listen to everyone else discuss our

359
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:21,544
Our due diligence of what we're doing for our children is very frustrating.

360
00:51:21,925 --> 00:51:24,188
I've said it to you before and I will say it to you again.

361
00:51:24,348 --> 00:51:25,849
Thank you for bringing this up to us.

362
00:51:26,230 --> 00:51:30,134
But you also have to understand that there is a process.

363
00:51:30,535 --> 00:51:33,678
I'm not saying that the process is behind closed doors.

364
00:51:33,999 --> 00:51:36,081
We haven't been in that situation in the past.

365
00:51:36,982 --> 00:51:38,243
And you're absolutely right.

366
00:51:38,283 --> 00:51:43,868
We've always talked about, if God forbid anything happens, that we want to know what's going to happen.

367
00:51:44,409 --> 00:51:53,316
But to sit here and know outside of this room that already there is people talking about, oh, we're hiring or we're firing, that's not fair to us.

368
00:51:53,877 --> 00:51:55,518
And I'm not saying that that was you.

369
00:51:56,058 --> 00:51:59,561
And I know that you have children in the system, because my children have been with your children.

370
00:52:00,342 --> 00:52:03,785
So I am not getting more aggravated at you.

371
00:52:03,945 --> 00:52:05,386
I thanked you for coming to us.

372
00:52:05,966 --> 00:52:10,069
But you need to give us, you, the public, needs to give us some time.

373
00:52:10,829 --> 00:52:14,052
Because there hasn't been time to sit down and do what we have to do.

374
00:52:14,392 --> 00:52:18,895
And it's kind of ironic, we can't evaluate something if you have nothing to evaluate it from.

375
00:52:19,596 --> 00:52:22,358
We have to evaluate the evening with the superintendent.

376
00:52:22,978 --> 00:52:27,300
Well, we have to wait for the evening of the superintendent, and that is coming up this week.

377
00:52:27,901 --> 00:52:32,763
So, I mean, I understand the frustration of everybody, but you also have to understand the frustration of us.

378
00:52:33,263 --> 00:52:37,125
Me, myself, as a parent, totally understand, but I'm on both sides.

379
00:52:37,785 --> 00:52:46,630
And it's very frustrating when you know your children are doing 100 percent the best they possibly can, and they're striving, and people just come to you and just

380
00:52:47,472 --> 00:52:49,893
keep on saying facts that are not true.

381
00:52:50,253 --> 00:52:54,855
If we're going to throw facts out there, let's remember, I don't know, a little bit of reality.

382
00:52:55,676 --> 00:52:57,857
And we sit here, I'm number one.

383
00:52:57,977 --> 00:53:01,418
I started here 10 years ago with let's not bully anybody.

384
00:53:02,219 --> 00:53:08,181
What kind of a message are we sending as adults to our children that we say don't bully?

385
00:53:08,501 --> 00:53:09,802
And we're at this point.

386
00:53:10,562 --> 00:53:11,683
It's very frustrating.

387
00:53:13,162 --> 00:53:13,862
Thank you.

388
00:53:13,882 --> 00:53:14,723
Mr. Benedetto.

389
00:53:15,163 --> 00:53:15,563
Thank you.

390
00:53:15,764 --> 00:53:17,665
Um, I don't agree with my colleague.

391
00:53:18,005 --> 00:53:23,288
First of all, when you came in April, I wish I had said something, but you did make me think.

392
00:53:23,768 --> 00:53:26,070
And I did request the superintendent's contract.

393
00:53:26,190 --> 00:53:32,474
And that's when I found out that as a school committee member, the June 30th date, I did not know that prior to that.

394
00:53:33,234 --> 00:53:41,999
And, um, I'm honest and truthful, but prior to that, there were discussions and there were requests and evaluation processes happening.

395
00:53:42,580 --> 00:53:42,740
So,

396
00:53:43,371 --> 00:53:47,835
That actual date of June 30th, knowing that, that's where that came about.

397
00:53:48,095 --> 00:53:49,276
And I brought it to a meeting.

398
00:53:49,985 --> 00:53:51,126
after you came forward.

399
00:53:51,606 --> 00:54:03,453
And I apologize because I know it's not easy to stand there in front of a body of people and a whole nother room full of people and just ask about a process and not making it personal.

400
00:54:03,593 --> 00:54:04,974
I do this all the time.

401
00:54:05,514 --> 00:54:10,037
I do it with asking for budgets and I do it for oh, so many things.

402
00:54:10,117 --> 00:54:12,279
And people think I'm like, what do you want to know?

403
00:54:13,019 --> 00:54:16,101
I just want to know what's happening so I can make good judgments.

404
00:54:16,621 --> 00:54:18,182
And I think that's what's happening here.

405
00:54:18,742 --> 00:54:19,483
I think that

406
00:54:20,097 --> 00:54:28,344
The stuff going on, the parents making comments and bring them up, most of them

407
00:54:29,558 --> 00:54:33,099
Not all of them, but most of them, about the process.

408
00:54:33,439 --> 00:54:34,219
What do we do?

409
00:54:34,719 --> 00:54:38,840
We've had a great run with Superintendent Bellson.

410
00:54:39,240 --> 00:54:41,901
We wouldn't have our science labs without him.

411
00:54:42,481 --> 00:54:43,141
I know that.

412
00:54:43,681 --> 00:54:45,101
I know that better than anyone.

413
00:54:45,261 --> 00:54:49,482
He came to this meeting and presented it, and it's amazing that we have that.

414
00:54:49,762 --> 00:54:52,923
That got one third of our high school building remodeled at the same time.

415
00:54:53,383 --> 00:55:00,289
I mean, I watched in awe as that happened in front of me and made sure that it expanded our whole vocational education.

416
00:55:00,369 --> 00:55:05,333
And he's done so many wonderful things, but that does not mean he's going to be here forever.

417
00:55:05,714 --> 00:55:07,695
And we do need to start the process.

418
00:55:08,176 --> 00:55:10,518
I have asked for his self-evaluation.

419
00:55:10,938 --> 00:55:15,122
As far as I've been told from him, he is going to provide that to us today.

420
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:18,885
May 16th is the date he told us at a prior meeting.

421
00:55:19,265 --> 00:55:21,447
I was looking forward to seeing that this evening.

422
00:55:21,752 --> 00:55:25,454
If that date has changed, he can correct me and tell me why that's changed.

423
00:55:25,775 --> 00:55:32,379
But we need sufficient time to go over his self-evaluation and do our evaluation that we do every year.

424
00:55:32,659 --> 00:55:33,719
We do this every year.

425
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:35,981
And every year, I talk about his strengths.

426
00:55:36,381 --> 00:55:41,064
And every year, I talk about areas of growth, just like anyone in any job.

427
00:55:41,804 --> 00:55:49,089
And whether or not he has the option of deciding whether he's coming back, but he doesn't have to tell us until September 1st.

428
00:55:49,209 --> 00:55:50,390
That's what the contract says.

429
00:55:51,150 --> 00:55:58,896
My obligation as a school committee member and to the people who voted me into this seat is to make sure you feel that it's transparent.

430
00:55:59,336 --> 00:56:06,221
If you ever have a question, I will answer it honestly as to the process and what happened in my eyes and in my viewpoint.

431
00:56:06,741 --> 00:56:08,943
So I commend you for being here.

432
00:56:09,703 --> 00:56:11,224
I know that we're going to move forward.

433
00:56:11,304 --> 00:56:14,046
I'm very happy to have the meeting on the second.

434
00:56:14,366 --> 00:56:19,090
I would like the superintendent's evaluation prior to that so we can provide our

435
00:56:20,272 --> 00:56:25,740
evaluations of him on that evening so that way we commit and meet our deadlines.

436
00:56:26,141 --> 00:56:36,055
And I would like it published in a way that all of our community understands that we're doing this like we did last year, like we did the year prior.

437
00:56:36,676 --> 00:56:45,018
I don't want to be disrespectful to a person, but I want the process to be more clear, more understandable.

438
00:56:45,778 --> 00:56:50,439
Maybe this year we want to—we've always had the opportunity for people to come and speak.

439
00:56:50,799 --> 00:56:57,541
We usually don't have that in our audience, and I'm glad to see that some people are here and lined up to speak.

