591
01:09:37,316 --> 01:09:38,497
So thank you for being here.

592
01:09:38,517 --> 01:09:39,017
Thank you.

593
01:09:39,817 --> 01:09:41,777
Mr. Superintendent would like to clarify some.

594
01:09:43,557 --> 01:09:44,378
Thank you, Madam Mayor.

595
01:09:46,538 --> 01:09:46,678
So,

596
01:09:48,668 --> 01:09:56,130
I've been here 21 years now as superintendent, 48 years as a public educator in the city of Medford.

597
01:09:56,750 --> 01:09:57,750
I grew up in the community.

598
01:09:57,950 --> 01:09:58,810
I went to the schools.

599
01:09:58,850 --> 01:09:59,950
I went to the Forest Park.

600
01:10:00,950 --> 01:10:02,491
I went to the Roberts Junior High School.

601
01:10:02,531 --> 01:10:03,611
I went to Medford High School.

602
01:10:05,671 --> 01:10:07,492
So this is my community.

603
01:10:08,392 --> 01:10:09,132
I care about it.

604
01:10:09,772 --> 01:10:18,334
And as I've said before, I never intend or would never intend to make a decision that would leave my community

605
01:10:18,962 --> 01:10:19,442
in the lurch.

606
01:10:21,082 --> 01:10:33,805
Now, having said that, we have had a process of evaluation and decision-making that has gone back well before my term as superintendent, and it's always been transparent.

607
01:10:35,625 --> 01:10:38,145
My self-evaluation will come to the committee this week.

608
01:10:39,346 --> 01:10:39,866
You'll have it.

609
01:10:40,446 --> 01:10:42,246
You'll have more than two weeks to go over it.

610
01:10:43,266 --> 01:10:47,287
That's a pretty substantial period of time to look at the document, which takes me time,

611
01:10:48,369 --> 01:10:54,151
to produce and review given all the other responsibilities that we have in the school district.

612
01:10:56,052 --> 01:10:57,533
The process will be in public.

613
01:10:58,293 --> 01:10:58,913
It always is.

614
01:11:00,274 --> 01:11:00,914
Open session.

615
01:11:00,954 --> 01:11:02,295
It's not an executive session.

616
01:11:02,375 --> 01:11:04,175
It's not away from anyone.

617
01:11:05,336 --> 01:11:13,159
It's open and every committee member has an opportunity to say what they feel and make whatever ratings they want to make.

618
01:11:14,280 --> 01:11:15,300
So far they've been good.

619
01:11:16,199 --> 01:11:22,501
I'm sure that there may be some things that people would like to see me do better, or the school system do better.

620
01:11:23,482 --> 01:11:25,202
But clearly, it's been an open process.

621
01:11:26,483 --> 01:11:39,608
And as you can tell, people come to the rail all the time and make statements, give their opinions, come into meetings, some of them in support, and some of them critical.

622
01:11:40,488 --> 01:11:41,609
But that's a balancing act.

623
01:11:41,889 --> 01:11:44,090
Wherever we are, that's what takes place.

624
01:11:46,585 --> 01:11:54,730
What does concern me is this, and I say this in a very sincere way, and that's simply this.

625
01:11:55,911 --> 01:12:10,319
Whether I stay or go, when I go, if an outside individual is going to consider the Medford Public Schools as his or her home, as superintendent, they are going to evaluate the environment.

626
01:12:11,260 --> 01:12:14,822
And if they feel the environment is hostile, they're not coming here.

627
01:12:16,318 --> 01:12:28,624
They're not coming here because it's a tough enough job not to be in a situation where people are divided and split along many issues.

628
01:12:29,744 --> 01:12:41,290
So it's our responsibility to have a decent dialogue, to make an appropriate decision, but to keep it intelligent and to keep it

629
01:12:42,667 --> 01:12:53,574
welcoming, so that when someone does consider applying for the Medford Public Schools, they say, I want to go there, because that's a good place to be a superintendent of schools.

630
01:12:54,054 --> 01:13:00,198
The people support the administration, they support their school committee, and there's mutual respect.

631
01:13:01,319 --> 01:13:03,240
And so that's really what we've got to strive for.

632
01:13:03,260 --> 01:13:05,702
A decision will be made.

633
01:13:07,095 --> 01:13:09,456
Decision will happen in public session.

634
01:13:09,476 --> 01:13:12,037
Decision will happen after a lot of consultation.

635
01:13:12,698 --> 01:13:21,942
And a lot of the things that we have to decide are based on, am I a person at this point in time able to bring forward our agenda in an intelligent way?

636
01:13:22,682 --> 01:13:26,244
Or is someone else maybe better positioned to do that at this point in time?

637
01:13:27,404 --> 01:13:28,064
That's what it's about.

638
01:13:29,405 --> 01:13:30,085
That's what it's about.

639
01:13:30,966 --> 01:13:34,527
So let's have our process.

640
01:13:34,967 --> 01:13:36,028
Let's respect each other.

641
01:13:36,893 --> 01:13:43,634
Let's continue to work together, and let's make a decision in a timely way on behalf of the community.

642
01:13:44,434 --> 01:13:46,315
Now, superintendent searches vary.

643
01:13:47,455 --> 01:13:49,975
Many of them are done in a lot shorter time than a year.

644
01:13:50,515 --> 01:13:56,917
But if that's the community's wish, then that's something we'd go forward with.

645
01:13:58,237 --> 01:14:04,258
But I've observed a lot of searches over the years, and people call me all the time because I've been around for a long time.

646
01:14:05,475 --> 01:14:09,696
So I think that it's important we go through our process.

