01:30:45,545 --> 01:30:46,405
and the city council.

903
01:30:46,845 --> 01:30:47,946
And that, oh, go ahead.

904
01:30:47,966 --> 01:30:49,506
I just want to say, Jean, you're a taxpayer.

905
01:30:50,167 --> 01:30:50,707
Yes, that's right.

906
01:30:51,007 --> 01:30:51,307
That's right.

907
01:30:51,387 --> 01:30:54,768
I mean, you're a taxpayer, so you don't have to keep on saying, I don't have kids in the system.

908
01:30:55,028 --> 01:30:55,888
You are a taxpayer.

909
01:30:55,908 --> 01:30:57,029
You are a citizen of Medford.

910
01:30:57,069 --> 01:31:03,871
You have every right to be concerned about the schools in our community as any other person, any parent, or whatever.

911
01:31:03,891 --> 01:31:04,331
Well, thank you.

912
01:31:04,491 --> 01:31:04,711
Thank you.

913
01:31:05,151 --> 01:31:06,312
So I just wanted to say that

914
01:31:07,897 --> 01:31:09,459
There's nothing wrong with asking the question.

915
01:31:09,739 --> 01:31:12,182
And I think that every five years, somebody should be judging you.

916
01:31:12,382 --> 01:31:12,782
No offense.

917
01:31:12,802 --> 01:31:13,283
Every year.

918
01:31:13,383 --> 01:31:13,844
Every year?

919
01:31:14,284 --> 01:31:15,405
Every year he's reviewed.

920
01:31:15,425 --> 01:31:17,528
But it should come from some higher authority and not yourself.

921
01:31:17,548 --> 01:31:18,669
Well, we are the higher authority.

922
01:31:18,729 --> 01:31:19,370
We hire him.

923
01:31:19,550 --> 01:31:20,090
Oh, you hire him.

924
01:31:20,130 --> 01:31:20,371
OK.

925
01:31:20,611 --> 01:31:20,891
All right.

926
01:31:20,931 --> 01:31:21,272
OK.

927
01:31:21,292 --> 01:31:22,473
Yeah, but he's evaluating himself.

928
01:31:22,533 --> 01:31:23,094
I don't get it.

929
01:31:23,114 --> 01:31:23,374
He should.

930
01:31:23,674 --> 01:31:25,136
He submits it to the body.

931
01:31:27,258 --> 01:31:27,418
Yeah.

932
01:31:27,498 --> 01:31:27,759
OK.

933
01:31:28,099 --> 01:31:28,379
All right.

934
01:31:29,995 --> 01:31:32,097
Well, that needs to happen, and it needs to be.

935
01:31:32,457 --> 01:31:33,758
And I'm all for having it open.

936
01:31:34,178 --> 01:31:38,701
The Charter Review, I'm all for open government, and I want to thank everybody for the transparency.

937
01:31:38,721 --> 01:31:40,022
It's a new day is dawning.

938
01:31:40,563 --> 01:31:41,884
You got a job in front of you.

939
01:31:42,024 --> 01:31:43,285
I don't envy you.

940
01:31:44,005 --> 01:31:45,766
And I'll see you guys later.

941
01:31:45,786 --> 01:31:45,987
Thank you.

942
01:31:46,167 --> 01:31:46,687
Thank you, Ms.

943
01:31:46,707 --> 01:31:47,047
Martin.

944
01:31:50,370 --> 01:31:50,530
Ms.

945
01:31:50,570 --> 01:31:50,930
Cuno?

946
01:31:51,290 --> 01:31:53,132
I just wanted to address what Gene said.

947
01:31:54,149 --> 01:31:55,249
I just want to make it very clear.

948
01:31:55,269 --> 01:31:56,650
I'm not trying to be defensive.

949
01:31:57,270 --> 01:32:02,631
I just get very frustrated between facts being thrown out and non-factual stuff being thrown out.

950
01:32:03,211 --> 01:32:05,551
And so I've gone to City Council.

951
01:32:05,591 --> 01:32:08,992
If you're going to be speaking about City Council, I've gone to City Council many, many times.

952
01:32:09,532 --> 01:32:13,593
And I try to get my information not only from City Council, but also from parents.

953
01:32:14,013 --> 01:32:16,814
When there's two stories out there, you always have to listen to both.

954
01:32:17,414 --> 01:32:23,175
And it got frustrating to me as a school committee member because we haven't had the opportunity yet

955
01:32:23,935 --> 01:32:26,778
until tonight to really speak about what is going on.

956
01:32:27,299 --> 01:32:37,609
So for that, I apologize if I come across being defensive, but I get very upset and very passionate when I know there's certain things that are not true and certain things that are.

957
01:32:38,150 --> 01:32:42,835
And as far as debating and coming and asking questions, that's why we're here.

958
01:32:43,215 --> 01:32:44,096
We're not here for us.

959
01:32:44,457 --> 01:32:45,458
We're here for everybody else.

960
01:32:47,319 --> 01:32:47,479
Ms.

961
01:32:47,499 --> 01:32:49,281
Vander Kloof?

962
01:32:49,321 --> 01:32:49,481
No.

963
01:32:49,962 --> 01:32:50,662
Mr. Benedetto.

964
01:32:51,503 --> 01:32:51,863
Thank you.

965
01:32:52,043 --> 01:32:52,504
I'm sorry.

966
01:32:53,044 --> 01:32:54,045
One, one, I'm sorry.

967
01:32:54,145 --> 01:32:54,866
One more quick thing.

968
01:32:55,327 --> 01:33:09,600
Um, I know this item, a few items have been on the city council agenda and some of our colleagues have moved over to city council and I just feel like we're working together because they have to approve the ultimate bar budget as well.

969
01:33:09,980 --> 01:33:16,004
So I believe that the school committee and the city council working together only benefits our community.

970
01:33:16,325 --> 01:33:22,609
And I look forward to doing that with them in a much more open, direct way.

971
01:33:23,049 --> 01:33:35,058
Because I feel like any kind, instead of it being them and us, I want it to be us working together as elected officials to represent all the voters and all the people coming forward.

972
01:33:35,458 --> 01:33:37,439
So I just want to say that straight out.

973
01:33:37,659 --> 01:33:42,422
And I'm glad that our items are on their agenda and someday maybe some of theirs might be on us.

974
01:33:42,603 --> 01:33:45,064
Absolutely, because they're in charge of the budget.

975
01:33:45,324 --> 01:33:46,425
So I totally agree with that.

976
01:33:47,345 --> 01:33:53,569
But I want to just say, instead of just one-on-one and cherry-picking, you know, that it needs to be body-to-body.

977
01:33:53,609 --> 01:33:59,533
We need to have the whole body of the city council sit down with the whole body of the school committee and maybe under new leadership we can do that.

978
01:34:00,193 --> 01:34:01,614
If you're doing the right thing, you will do that.

979
01:34:01,954 --> 01:34:02,595
Thank you very much.

980
01:34:05,768 --> 01:34:06,809
Hello, your name, please.

981
01:34:07,349 --> 01:34:08,369
My name is Bob Candy.

982
01:34:08,990 --> 01:34:11,091
And Monique DeVos, Grand Ave.

983
01:34:11,831 --> 01:34:14,372
Monique and I have three children in the system.

984
01:34:16,333 --> 01:34:20,556
Abby is now actually at Mount Holyoke, so I shouldn't say we've had three children in the system.

985
01:34:22,296 --> 01:34:24,418
She prospered in the Medford schools.

986
01:34:25,598 --> 01:34:33,362
Ben is number one in his class this year and doing very well, taking advantage of AP courses.

987
01:34:34,123 --> 01:34:34,943
Things are going great.

988
01:34:37,042 --> 01:34:44,224
and Jane is prospering as well as a freshman, we're not here tonight to talk about Mr. Belson.

989
01:34:45,805 --> 01:34:49,507
And I don't know why this has been conflated with Mr. Belson.

990
01:34:50,807 --> 01:35:01,411
This is not, when you talk about a time for a process, and by the way, I appreciate your motion, or some of the comments that have been made, it makes no sense to us.

991
01:35:01,872 --> 01:35:05,033
With all due respect, I don't mean this the wrong way, it could be Mickey Mouse up there.

992
01:35:06,007 --> 01:35:07,187
It doesn't matter.

993
01:35:07,527 --> 01:35:09,428
A succession plan is a plan.

994
01:35:10,008 --> 01:35:12,189
It's irrespective of who's in place.

995
01:35:13,669 --> 01:35:20,071
Whether Mr. Belson decides he wants to renew, retire, God forbid he's ill, doesn't matter.

996
01:35:20,952 --> 01:35:25,453
And what hasn't been done, at least as far as Monique and I can tell, is you don't have a plan.

997
01:35:26,613 --> 01:35:29,674
And it's not dependent on what Mr. Belson decides to do.

998
01:35:29,874 --> 01:35:31,175
It's just good common sense.

999
01:35:32,355 --> 01:35:35,096
I've checked other school districts before we got here.

1000
01:35:36,657 --> 01:35:38,958
You'd be amazed how many school districts have a plan.

1001
01:35:39,858 --> 01:35:45,220
Indeed, there's a quote from one of them that says, the lack of a plan is no plan at all.

1002
01:35:46,500 --> 01:35:53,502
So with that said, this is not a referendum on the elephant in the room, I think, as you put it, Ms.

1003
01:35:53,522 --> 01:35:54,102
Vander Kloot.

1004
01:35:54,662 --> 01:36:03,205
Whether Mr. Belson goes, stays, how well he's done, it's a separate issue to be determined by the school committee, by the parents,

1005
01:36:04,462 --> 01:36:07,824
all concerned, we want to talk about the succession plan.

1006
01:36:09,886 --> 01:36:14,409
In the corporate world, the schools would be the public company.

1007
01:36:15,450 --> 01:36:17,911
The taxpayers would be your investors.

1008
01:36:18,192 --> 01:36:20,893
Stop me if this analogy isn't working for you.

1009
01:36:22,675 --> 01:36:28,439
The shareholders are the Medford taxpayers who want to see a return on their investment.

1010
01:36:29,339 --> 01:36:31,081
Many of us are parents here of children.

1011
01:36:31,241 --> 01:36:33,062
We want to see them achieve their potential.

1012
01:36:34,055 --> 01:36:37,697
And we want the schools to continue to improve their accountability results.

1013
01:36:39,118 --> 01:36:42,300
The school committee is the company's board of directors.

1014
01:36:43,561 --> 01:36:50,365
And in the corporate world, they're charged with ensuring responsible governance and the ongoing continuity of the company.

1015
01:36:51,426 --> 01:37:00,612
If a company that was public did not have a succession plan, they would be guilty of malfeasance and could be charged by their shareholders and by the government.

1016
01:37:01,605 --> 01:37:04,886
with failing to adhere to several statutes that I can think of.

1017
01:37:06,466 --> 01:37:12,327
So why this is such a matter of contention, we don't get this.

1018
01:37:12,707 --> 01:37:15,948
Whether you were defensive or not, I know it's difficult, Ms.

1019
01:37:15,968 --> 01:37:17,108
Cunha, to sit and listen.

1020
01:37:18,609 --> 01:37:20,709
Our sons run track together.

1021
01:37:20,769 --> 01:37:24,190
We appreciate everything that you do, all of you, day in and day out.

1022
01:37:24,970 --> 01:37:25,730
It's not about this.

1023
01:37:26,490 --> 01:37:29,811
So hearing this is really troubling.

1024
01:37:30,462 --> 01:37:31,883
you're either going to do the right thing.

1025
01:37:32,603 --> 01:37:35,285
And I'm sorry if you don't like that phrase, or you're not.

1026
01:37:38,607 --> 01:37:44,650
So the board is also responsible for ensuring the school committee the performance of the CEO.

1027
01:37:46,231 --> 01:37:48,612
And in this analogy, obviously, that's Mr. Belson.

1028
01:37:50,233 --> 01:37:53,515
Him meeting the standards that you define and that he defines for himself.

1029
01:37:53,575 --> 01:37:57,497
He's not going to, I'm sure, define standards he doesn't think he should be meeting.

1030
01:37:58,531 --> 01:38:02,294
And finding out if he doesn't do that, as someone pointed out, holding him accountable.

1031
01:38:03,435 --> 01:38:04,756
It shouldn't matter who is at the helm.

1032
01:38:05,737 --> 01:38:23,311
So the goal of the shareholders, the parents, the community at large, is it fair to ask if you folks really feel that you know, as your shareholders, what the parents and the community at large really want from the district?

1033
01:38:23,792 --> 01:38:26,014
Do you feel you truly understand that?

1034
01:38:26,414 --> 01:38:27,595
Have you done any surveys?

1035
01:38:28,650 --> 01:38:31,032
I know you talk to parents all the time, God knows.

1036
01:38:31,933 --> 01:38:37,237
You know, Paulette, she's everywhere and does a great job, and I know the rest of you do, too.

1037
01:38:37,357 --> 01:38:38,377
But do you know that?

1038
01:38:38,498 --> 01:38:39,538
Have you actually polled them?

1039
01:38:39,578 --> 01:38:46,384
Have you spoken with them in a matter that you could publish and say, you know what, the majority of people seem to want A, B, C, D?

1040
01:38:47,965 --> 01:38:50,567
Because the succession plan is supposed to have that, by the way.

1041
01:38:50,607 --> 01:38:54,209
It's not just supposed to be about replacing Mr. Belson should he leave or go.

1042
01:38:54,790 --> 01:38:56,031
It's supposed to be about

1043
01:38:56,544 --> 01:39:05,929
We need a plan to achieve X with a person who's going to hold this job, who's capable of doing A, B, C, D, E, except the A through E ain't there.

1044
01:39:05,949 --> 01:39:09,631
At least not as far as we know.

1045
01:39:11,012 --> 01:39:14,414
So what about the goals of the teachers and the other staff?

1046
01:39:14,494 --> 01:39:19,696
I see them all here tonight, and I'm really glad they're expressing support for Mr. Belson, but again, this isn't about him.

1047
01:39:20,897 --> 01:39:26,280
This is about governance, simple governance.

1048
01:39:27,459 --> 01:39:29,100
What about the goals of the administration?

1049
01:39:29,280 --> 01:39:30,120
Mr. Belson's right.

1050
01:39:30,160 --> 01:39:34,743
He has a perfect right to define what we should be doing as a school system.

1051
01:39:35,723 --> 01:39:37,244
And that should be for Ms.

1052
01:39:37,284 --> 01:39:38,084
Caldwell and Ms.

1053
01:39:38,124 --> 01:39:39,305
Nelson and the principals.

1054
01:39:40,565 --> 01:39:41,586
But it's not in a plan.

1055
01:39:42,846 --> 01:39:43,647
Not that we know of.

1056
01:39:43,727 --> 01:39:44,787
Not a succession plan.

1057
01:39:46,128 --> 01:39:50,890
And it should be based on all of the above and you should have a recruiting plan for it regardless of why.

1058
01:39:50,910 --> 01:39:52,651
It should be there.

1059
01:39:53,011 --> 01:39:56,373
You should know, Mr. Belson said, some take longer, some don't.

1060
01:39:58,337 --> 01:39:59,497
Just have the plan.

1061
01:40:00,818 --> 01:40:06,340
So telling me that there's good superintendents, I know that.

1062
01:40:06,580 --> 01:40:07,260
We work with Ms.

1063
01:40:07,300 --> 01:40:08,361
Caldwell in particular.

1064
01:40:08,561 --> 01:40:09,201
She's excellent.

1065
01:40:09,901 --> 01:40:15,624
But that said, knowing that you have people in place, that's a contingency.

1066
01:40:15,824 --> 01:40:16,804
That's not a plan.

1067
01:40:18,485 --> 01:40:18,945
Am I wrong?

1068
01:40:22,206 --> 01:40:22,406
OK.

1069
01:40:23,027 --> 01:40:24,587
I just wanted to know I was in office.

1070
01:40:24,647 --> 01:40:26,048
My wife tells me in outer space.

1071
01:40:29,785 --> 01:40:30,025
Okay.

1072
01:40:30,646 --> 01:40:33,487
So look, Monique and I really appreciate you listening to us.

1073
01:40:33,627 --> 01:40:35,729
We're already going in the step in the right direction.

1074
01:40:36,649 --> 01:40:41,252
So the dates kind of don't matter to us, but the good plan really does.

1075
01:40:41,772 --> 01:40:47,516
We would ask you to find a mechanism to survey the parents and the community at large.

1076
01:40:48,096 --> 01:40:53,880
It's unfortunate we don't get as many people as we could, but you and I both know, not a lot of people show up.

1077
01:40:54,398 --> 01:41:01,564
Same people to the PTO, same people to the meetings, but there's a lot of good-hearted parents out there who give you information if you ask for it.

1078
01:41:02,445 --> 01:41:09,191
So, Monique, I don't know if you have anything you want to add, but it's unusual.

1079
01:41:09,992 --> 01:41:11,453
We thank you for listening to us.

1080
01:41:11,473 --> 01:41:12,614
Do you have any questions of us?

1081
01:41:14,747 --> 01:41:14,927
Ms.

1082
01:41:14,947 --> 01:41:15,467
Van de Kloot?

1083
01:41:16,067 --> 01:41:39,016
So, Bob, one thing I just want to mention to you is that our thinking actually isn't that far apart, because recently I attended the National School Board Conference, and I said to Anne Marie, who was with me at the time, come on, come on, we have to go down and talk to these people, because the topic was how to successfully survey your school population so it's meaningful.

1084
01:41:39,796 --> 01:41:43,217
And so that's very much been part of my thinking of sort of saying that it is time

1085
01:41:43,650 --> 01:41:45,871
I believe, to reach out and to send a survey.

1086
01:41:45,911 --> 01:41:50,334
But, you know, surveys can be useless and they can be powerful.

1087
01:41:50,814 --> 01:41:54,917
And that's, so that was my thinking about that.

1088
01:41:55,177 --> 01:42:00,680
I do want to mention to you also that we do establish goals every fall.

1089
01:42:00,920 --> 01:42:02,541
We talk about them publicly.

1090
01:42:02,601 --> 01:42:04,302
We argue about them.

1091
01:42:04,422 --> 01:42:06,263
And those are our guiding lights.

1092
01:42:06,763 --> 01:42:10,766
Again, personally, I think now we're clearly at the place where we need a succession,

1093
01:42:11,807 --> 01:42:16,392
to talk about this and I will just assure you that it will happen.

1094
01:42:16,532 --> 01:42:17,113
Can I ask a question?

1095
01:42:17,574 --> 01:42:17,834
Sure.

1096
01:42:17,994 --> 01:42:19,496
Do parents have to live to your goals?

1097
01:42:20,577 --> 01:42:21,518
I certainly think they should.

1098
01:42:21,918 --> 01:42:22,259
Do they?

1099
01:42:24,257 --> 01:42:25,077
Do they have input?

1100
01:42:25,478 --> 01:42:28,038
Well, Bob, you know, every year we do it.

1101
01:42:28,338 --> 01:42:30,959
Every year, you know, we have three people in the audience.

1102
01:42:31,259 --> 01:42:40,682
So let me suggest, knowing that, because we both know that that's the case, that what you just did, going to find out what that is, find a better mechanism.

1103
01:42:41,282 --> 01:42:42,822
Don't rely upon people to show up.

1104
01:42:42,842 --> 01:42:43,723
You know they're not going to do it.

1105
01:42:44,763 --> 01:42:48,604
You guys are given all these nights and you must obviously feel very tired about it.

1106
01:42:49,028 --> 01:42:55,251
But I'll bet you that if you gave people an online mechanism to respond that was anonymous, if you need help with that, let me know.

1107
01:42:56,271 --> 01:42:56,812
It can be done.

1108
01:42:57,812 --> 01:42:59,273
With that said, a last comment.

